import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x=data['distance'])
    plt.axvline(x=data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].mean()))
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['origin_destination'] = data['origin'] + ' to ' + data['destination']
    top_airports = data['origin_destination'].value_counts().nlargest(10)
    chart = sns.barplot(x=top_airports.index, y=top_airports.values)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('Which airports have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    flights_per_day = data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='flights')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='flights', data=flights_per_day)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
